        <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2011-07-15T19:13:49Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Older Driver and Pedestrian Safety and Roadway Enhancement Act of 2011 - Directs the Secretary of Transportation (DOT) to implement a roadway safety enhancement program for older drivers and pedestrians to: (1) improve roadway safety infrastructure in states that is consistent with recommendations of the Federal Highway Administration (FHWA) in the &quot;Highway Design Handbook for Older Drivers and Pedestrians,&quot; and (2) achieve significant reductions in roadway fatalities and serious injuries among drivers and pedestrians 65 years old or older on all public roads.</p> <p>Sets forth project eligibility requirements and project identification and selection priorities.</p> <p>Requires the Secretary to finalize revision of the Handbook for publication.</p> <p>Amends the Safe, Accountable, Flexible, Efficient Transportation Act: A Legacy for Users (SAFETEA-LU) to repeal its program for roadway safety improvements for older drivers and pedestrians.</p> <p>Requires the Secretary to: (1) appoint a Special Assistant for Older Driver and Pedestrian Safety within the Office of the Secretary; and (2) establish national goals for increasing driver, passenger, and pedestrian safety for persons 65 years old or older.</p> <p>Requires the Secretary to revise the manual on uniform traffic control devices to include a standard for a minimum level of retroreflectivity for pavement markings on all public roads.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
